President Barack Obama released a statement on the passing of Arnold Palmer, recognizing his impact on the sport of golf and his contributions beyond the game. Palmer's humble beginnings and his fearless approach to the game inspired a generation of golfers. The President also highlighted Palmer's generosity and his commitment to giving back to the community. The statement concludes with President Obama and First Lady Michelle Obama expressing their condolences and standing with Palmer's fans, known as "Arnie's Army," in honoring his legacy.